HEADWORD: Ironbark tree
<hw>I"ron*bark` tree`</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The Australian <spn>Eucalyptus
Sideroxylon</spn>, used largely by carpenters and shipbuilders; --
called also <altname>ironwood</altname>. Also applied to other
Australian eucalyptuses with a hard, solid bark</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ironbound</ent>⟦br⟧
